<a href="javascript:card_browser(843)">The Balrog, Durin&#39;s Bane</a>     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> I bid around 1-3 burdens to start off. In my deck my Hobbits and Men try to just get there, while my Nazgul cut down the fellowship and load conditions on them. <br>
<br>
Shadow <br>
With drawn to its power and it wants to be found  I can add burdens for my last site which lets me draw a card for every burden. The Morgul Skulkers recycle my Nazgul and I have Lemenyas so when a Nazgul skirmishes a Super Charged guy like Aragorn, he puts a condition on him.  Then Lemenya gets out there with his sword and and makes him strength -2.  Really I have the Pale blade just so I can put it on the Witch King and make him as powerful as the Balrog.  Its really fun.<br>
<br>
Free Peoples <br>
I have armor or a coat of mail for Aragorn(depending on the deck) to protect him when I get swarmed or am fighting a damage +1 minion. I also can do that with Valiant man of the West. Incase he or Boromir is swarmed by like 4 minions I have a lot of strengtheners to put them away. I also have 3 hobbit swords so I can get them out fast for Frodo and Merry. Even though I may go first I can still pull a pathfinder to play my sites 2 and 3. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23867"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23867" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
